Even though I'm not a psychologist, I develop novel statistical methods for analyzing brain imaging data, so I have a very good understanding of mental illness. So I did what every reasonable scientist would do and I went down the list of diagnostic categories in the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders (DSM-V). I pieced it together that he has undiagnosed borderline PD, since he met 9 out of 9 criteria. What I missed was the narcissistic PD and antisocial PD (i.e., sociopathy). You see, the DSM is a broken diagnostic system that seems to be right only twice a month
